00:02:27.686 --> 00:02:29.229
And now what's nice is, we can look

00:02:29.229 --> 00:02:30.772
at our integration properties.

00:02:30.772 --> 00:02:32.639
This right over here,

00:02:32.639 --> 00:02:34.507
we could take these coefficients out.

00:02:34.507 --> 00:02:36.691
We could take this a-sub-1,

00:02:36.691 --> 00:02:38.496
put it in front of the integral sign.

00:02:38.496 --> 00:02:39.722
The a-sub-2, put it in front

00:02:39.722 --> 00:02:40.698
of the integral sign.

00:02:40.698 --> 00:02:42.203
The b-sub-1, put it in front

00:02:42.203 --> 00:02:43.665
of the integral sign.

00:02:43.665 --> 00:02:44.761
And then all you're left with is

00:02:44.761 --> 00:02:46.300
an integral from 0 to 2π

00:02:46.300 --> 00:02:47.741
of cosine of

00:02:47.741 --> 00:02:50.324
some integer multiple of t, dt.

00:02:51.485 --> 00:02:54.287
Well, we established
a couple of videos ago

00:02:54.287 --> 00:02:56.811
well, that's always
going to be equal to 0.

